HEADWORD: Hydroferricyanic
<hw>Hy`dro*fer`ri*cy*an"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 2 + <ets>ferricyanic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or containing, or obtained from,
hydrogen, ferric iron, and cyanogen; <as>as, <ex>hydroferricyanic</ex>
acid</as>. See <er>Ferricyanic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
